-- Colombian Stocks: Canacol Energy, Petrominerales Are Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-03-30T20:44:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/colombian-stock-movers-canacol-energy-ecopetrol-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.8 percent to 15,038.26. The Colcap
Index declined 0.4 percent to 1,743.63.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)   plunged 14 percent to 1,400
pesos, the biggest drop in 11 months. The Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  Colombia  said it has abandoned
an exploration well in the Andaquies block. “It confirms our
concern in the outlook of production for the mid-term,”
analysts Maria Adelaida Velasquez and Juan David Pineros of
brokerage Interbolsa SA said in a research report today.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMGC)  (PMGC CB), a Calgary-based company that
explores for and produces oil in Colombia, climbed 2.5 percent
to 33,280 pesos. Petrominerales rose in line with crude prices
in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
